<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4683&amp;p=41155#p41155"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">tomaitheous wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br /><div class="quotetitle">skrasms wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">but the sound engine has that nasty retrigger any time the upper 4 frequency bits update.<br /></div><br /><br /> I'm not familiar with this side effect( not vibrato, I know what that is). You get some sort of unwanted sound artifact when updating the period system at a higher rate or something?</div><br /><br />Oops, I meant upper 3 frequency bits. The upper 0.75 nibbles of frequency data  <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=":wink:" title="Wink" /> <br /><br />Anytime registers $4007 or $4003 are written it resets other aspects of the sound. The envelopes restart, for example. To do vibrato by direct pitch data changes it's fine starting on a pitch that isn't near an MSB change. In that case it's safe just writing $4002 and $4006. It's those crosses into MSB territory that cause issues.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3470">skrasms</a> — Tue Dec 30, 2008 11:59 pm</p><hr />
